##
## Introduction
##
@node introduction "LevelManDoor Guide: Introduction"


 INTRODUCTION
 ============
 
 'LevelMan' is a neat "little" program to be used as a door for MAX's BBS (and
 compatible programs).
 
 Features:      - handles user request/withdrawal of new access level
                - handles sysop options to grant/revoke/set/delete request
                - simple menu system
                - request list for sysop
                - config program included
                - add your own BBS banner.
 
 Added   :      - userid profiles
                - withdraw request.

 My intention was to create a quick & dirty version first, but as I got into
 it more coding was done for it, and features/options grew with it.
                                
 Anyway, enjoy it.
    
@endnode

##
## Installation
##
@node installation "LevelManDoor Guide: Installation"


  INSTALLATION
  ============
  
  Follow this checklist :
  
    1) add in s:user-startup:
    
            assign DOORS: your-doors-dir:          (if not already done)

    2) create a 'LevelMan' directory in 'DOORS:':
    
            cd doors:
            makedir levelman
    
    3) copy the LevelMan distribution to 'DOORS:LevelMan/'
    
    4) run @{"LevelDef" link leveldef } to define your configuration
          
    5) Alter MAX's menu config to add the door:
  
       Key   Func   Extra    LoAcc  HiAcc    Filename
       --------------------------------------------------------------
       R     34     0        0      10000    DOORS:LevelMan/LevelMan
       --------------------------------------------------------------     
             
    6) Alter the required menu/door text

    7) Alter the 'DOORS:LevelMan/LevelMan.text' file to your BBS needs
    
    8) Alter the help files to your BBS needs: LevelHeS.text, and the
       file 'LevelHeU.text'
      
    9) Define the profile userids in MAX's user editor (tip: add a password
       even you can't remember) [What are Profiles ? See @{"LevelDef" link leveldef }]
         
    10) All done ! Play...
     
             
  Now, you(r) (users) can request with this proggy and you can handle these !
      
  
@endnode

##
## Usage
##
@node usage "LevelManDoor Guide: Usage LevelMan"


  USAGE LEVELMAN
  ==============
  
  Purpose: - Sysop mode -> validate requests
                           delete requests
                           online help
                                                      
           - User mode  -> post/withdraw requests
                           online help                
                
  Options: - None

  Limits : - number of levels = max. 255
           - a level name     = max. 40 characters
           - access 10000     = reserved to Sysop = ALMIGHTY SYSOP!
           - a user can only withdraw a request once, it is not possible
             to delete a previous request after leaving the door.
              
  Detail :
   
          -> General:
          
             'LevelMan' will handle level change request from users, for the
             Sysop it functions as a request handler. 
             
             This door contains a seperate menu for Sysop or User, this is
             determined automatically by the program on execution. [1]
             
             First, a banner will be shown (in this version this is the same
             for both modes). This banner may be normal text or ANSI. It is
             located in "DOORS:LevelMan/LevelMan.Text". Adapt this to your
             BBS style.
             
             There is no need to create 2 menu entries in MAX's, one single
             will do (see [1]).
             
             Also, there are two 'Online Help' files (ANSI or normal text):
             
                         LevelHeS.Text  -> sysop
                         LevelHeU.Text  -> users 
             
          -> Sysop mode:
          
             The menu contains following choices:
             
                         Help     - online help
                         Process  - handle a request
                         Cleanup  - reorganize datafile
                         Quit     - kaboem!
                         
             The Sysop will handle access request in following manner:
             
                1) Select 'P'rocess request
                2) Select a request from the on screen list
                3) 'G'rant, 'R'evoke, 'S'et or 'D'elete the request.
                4) Confirm the choice
                
             Handling requests types:
             
                         Grant    - agree with level change
                         Revoke   - don't agree with level change
                         Set      - agree but only to the specified level
                         Delete   - for maintenance.            

  *NEW*      When Granting/Setting to a new access the users profile is
             copied from a default defined userid so that some values 
             related to that level are copied. 'LevelDef' will ask for this
             profile userid. Note: check expire days, set to zero.
             
             Following items are taken from the profile userid:
             
                Access Level
                U/D ratios
                Read/Write flags
                U/D flags
                Time Limit
                Max Bank Limit.
                
             Cleanup: this function will cleanup the datafile and delete
                      the 'Deleted' request. This is automatically done
                      when the Sysop leaves the door. However, when many
                      requests are alive/handled, he/she may want to do
                      it after handling some requests [and this way shorten
                      the online list when selecting].
                                                
          -> User mode:
          
             The menu contains following choices:
             
                         Help     - online help
                         Request  - enter a request
                         Withdraw - withdraw the entered request
                         Quit     - pataat!
                         
             The user will request as follows:
             
                1) Select 'R'equest
                2) Enter access level wanted
                
             The user can only withdraw a request in the same door call.
                            
          Should be a breeze to work with it. Anyway, there is online help 
          for your daft users.
                
   
   Errors:
   
   
   MESSAGE                                  DESCRIPTION/SOLUTION
   =====================================    =====================================
   LevelDef requires at least Kickstart     Obvious. Upgrade ! 
   2.04
   =====================================    =====================================
   Banner file not found, warn Sysop        Check assigns + LevelMan.Text
   =====================================    =====================================
   Config file not found, warn Sysop        Check assigns + LevelMan.Cfg  
   =====================================    =====================================
   Config file version fault, warn Sysop    You are using a config file of an old
                                            version. Regenerate using 'LevelDef'
   =====================================    =====================================          
   Error accessing datafile                 Datafile corrupted, delete it.
   =====================================    =====================================
   Couldn't create datafile, warn Sysop     Check assigns + directories,etc
   =====================================    =====================================
   Config error [LevelMan][NumberOfLevel    Config file incomplete, generate with
                                            'LevelDef'
   =====================================    =====================================
            
                                             
   TECHNICAL NOTES
   ---------------
   
   - I used the safest method of accessing the datafile, thus every change the
     file needs to be opened/closed. Shouldn't give an overhead since record size
     is quite small.
     
   - I've added simple file version control, not really necessary. This to make
     future enhancements easy. Eg. convert your old config/datafile to the new
     one as it appears. [As of v1.0 and onwards, v0.9 excluded]
     
     
                                                                   
@endnode

##
## LevelDef
##
@node leveldef "LevelManDoor Guide: Usage LevelDef"


  USAGE LEVELDEF
  ==============

  Purpose: create configuration for LevelMan.
  
  Options: FORCE/S  overwrite old existing configuration.
           
  Limits : - number of levels = max. 255
           - a level name     = max. 40 characters
           - an access        = 0 upto 9999 (SYSOP = 10000)
                    
  Example : 
             ------------------ cut ---------------------
             
             *     LevelDef V1.0 By Chris De Maeyer    *
             *  (c) 1997 Visionary Software - GIFTWARE *
          
             We will now set the default values...
             
             How many levels do you have (excl.Sysop): 3
             
             Now we will set the levels...
             [NOTE: level 1 = lowest (fe. Guest)
             
             Enter name level     [1]: Guest
             Enter access level   [1]: 5
   *NEW*     Enter profile level  [1]: Level_Profile1
             Enter name level     [2]: Member
             Enter access level   [2]: 10
   *NEW*     Enter profile level  [2]: Level_Profile2
             Enter name level     [3]: Co-sysop 
             Enter access level   [3]: 5000
   *NEW*     Enter profile level  [3]: Level_Profile3
           
   *NEW *    We will enter the path + filenames...
             
   *NEW*     Enter datafile      [eg. DOORS:Levelman/LevelMan.data]
   *NEW*     Enter bannerfile    [eg. DOORS:Levelman/Levelman.text]
   *NEW*     Enter Sysop help    [eg. DOORS:Levelman/LevelHeS.text]
   *NEW*     Enter Users help    [eg. DOORS:Levelman/LevelHeU.text]
   *NEW*     Enter Temp file     [eg. DOORS:Levelman/Levelman.tmp]
   *NEW*     Enter User index    [eg. BBS:UserFiles/User.index]
   *NEW*     Enter User data     [eg. BBS:UserFiles/User.data]
             
             Configuration complete !
             
             ------------------ cut ---------------------

   NOTE: path/filenames will be asked via filerequester.      
          
   
   Detail config parameters: (recommended values -> see example above)
   =========================
   
        Name Level 
        
                 the symbolic name you use on your BBS to make a distinct
                 group (fe. Guest, Member, Privileged, Co-sysop, etc)
        
        Access Level
        
                 the access level (as used in normal configuration) of the
                 level
                 
        Profile Level
         
                 the profile userid you will have to create, which denotes
                 the particular flags + settings of the level
   
        Datafile
        
                 the Levelman request database
                 
        Bannerfile
        
                 the screen used to display the menus (plain text or ANSI)
                 
        Sysop Help
        
                 the screen file for Sysop online help
                 
        Users Help
        
                 the screen file for User online help
                 
        Temp file
        
                 filename which levelman uses to perform its cleanup
                                              
        User Index
        
                 filename of MAX's User.index
                 
        User Data
        
                 filename of MAX's User.data
                                                                                  
   Errors:
   =======
   
   MESSAGE                                  DESCRIPTION/SOLUTION
   =====================================    =====================================
   LevelDef requires at least Kickstart     Obvious. Upgrade ! 
   2.04
   =====================================    =====================================
   Path DOORS:LevelMan not found            Did you 'assign DOORS:' ?
                                            Did you 'makedir DOORS:LevelMan' ?
   =====================================    =====================================
                    
@endnode

##
## Bugs
##
@node bugs "LevelManDoor Guide: Known problems & bugs"


  KNOWN PROBLEMS & BUGS
  =====================
  
  *LEVELDEF*
  
  - No conversion program has been added for updating your config file.
    You are advised to recreate it and not to edit it manually.
  
  *LEVELMAN*
  
  - this program can only be run as a door, running it as a CLI program
    will *** CRASH *** your system. 
          
@endnode

##
## History
##
@node history "LevelManDoor Guide: History"

   V1.0 (01-03-97)
   ===============
   
   *LEVELMAN*   - all path/filenames are configurable (except config file)
                - added userid profile support
                - WITHDRAW user option implemented
                - fixed index_User() function, now case insensitive
                - bumped required system libraries to V38
                - sysop list now includes status of requests
                                   
   *LEVELDEF*   - added selection of path/filenames with ASL requester
                - added config logic for userid profiles
                - removed LIST/S option
   

   V0.9 (05-02-97)
   ===============
   
   *LEVELMAN*   - this was the first BETA version
   
   *LEVELDEF*   - dito
   
@endnode

